	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Williamsport</placeName> <date>April 22. 5626</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">It was my duty<lb/> to write to you before this and to inform<lb/> you of some particulars resp. congre&#45;<lb/>gationational affairs but there were more<lb/> news to communicate of which I<lb/> could not speak before this time&#44; so<lb/> I had to postpone writing till to&#45;day<lb/> and I hope for this reason you will<lb/> excuse me.</p>
				<p>You will not be surprised to hear<lb/> that since shortly after my arrival<lb/> at <hi rend="underline"><placeName>Wmspt</placeName></hi>. I paid my attention to<lb/> <persName>Miss Amelia E. Ulman</persName> because I found<lb/> that all my hopes and imaginations<lb/> were centered in her and was lucky<lb/> enough to gain <persName>Miss Ulman&#39;s</persName> affections<lb/> in return. To&#45;night we are going</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>to celebrate our betrothal and we<lb/> appointed our wedding&#45;day to be<lb/> <add>Hebrew</add> It is <persName>Miss Ulman&#39;s</persName> as well<lb/> as my greatest wish that you would<lb/> be kind enough to come to <hi rend="underline"><placeName>Wmspt</placeName></hi>. to<lb/> perform the marriage ceremony for<lb/> us.</p>
				<p>At the same time I can inform you<lb/> that we had an examination of the<lb/> Hebrew and German School together<lb/> with an exhibition of the Sabbath<lb/> School on the first day of <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> which went off very nicely and to the<lb/> greatest satisfaction of all the members<lb/> of the Congregation. The children are<lb/> all doing right well and would be<lb/> worthy noticing those who excelled&#44; but<lb/> since you are not personally acquainted<lb/> with them it may not be so interesting<lb/> to you.</p>
				<p>Our new Congregation is also doing right<lb/> well and since there is County Court</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>held here this week will be chartered<lb/> and have the name <add>Hebrew</add>.<lb/> We have an addition of one family<lb/> from <placeName>Scranton</placeName> and expect another<lb/> here shortly.</p>
				<p>In expectation of an answer I<lb/> remain</p> 
			<p rend="indent(9)">Yours truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">J S Jacobson</persName></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. I Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dr Sir</p>
				<p>I intended to write to<lb/> you some time ago to inform you how<lb/> we are getting along with our Congregation<lb/> &#38;c&#44; but could not get time even for a<lb/> few moments to do so&#59; since <persName>Mr Jacobson</persName><lb/> has written and informed you of the par&#45;<lb/>ticulars it is not <sic>nessessary</sic> for me to do so<lb/> but sanction all he says&#59; Father &#38; Mother<lb/> send kindest regards to you and same of</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)">Yours &#38;c <persName role="author">Amelia E. Ulman</persName></p>
		</body>
